subSubSection.paragraph:
DIAGNOSIS: Males of 

O. ampulla

can be recognized by the wide clypeus, rectangular in dorsal view (
Fig. 38
), the proximally strongly enlarged bulbus (
Fig. 43, 45
, 
54
) and the endites with the distal tip a short outward-curving hook (
Fig. 52
). Females can be recognized by the combination of abdomen with a short extension (
Fig. 42
) and the genital area resembling a light bulb, as seen through the cuticle (
Fig. 48
).
